				///GREAT PERSON

  {
    "name": "Great Courtesan",
    "unitType": "Civilian",
    "uniques": [
         "Comment [-A master of charm, influence, and carefully calculated affection.\nKings emptied treasuries for them. Generals started wars over them. Senators ruined careers trying to impress them.\nWhether serving as diplomat, confidant, or professional destroyer of good judgment, their talents can reshape the fate of an empire.\n• Great Person]",
         "Empire enters a [10]-turn Golden Age <by consuming this unit>",
         "Free Great Person <by consuming this unit>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Village] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Trading post] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Fort] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Great Person - [Libertinage]",
         "Unbuildable",
         "Uncapturable"
    ],
    "movement": 3
  },
{
    "name": "Great Artist",
    "unitType": "Civilian",
    "uniques": [
         "Comment [-Poets, sculptors, playwrights, and other specialists in turning patron funding into immortality.\nTheir works inspire the masses, glorify rulers, and occasionally conceal political criticism well enough to avoid execution.\nWhile armies conquer cities, artists conquer memory. One tends to last longer.\n• Great Person]",
         "Empire enters a [10]-turn Golden Age <by consuming this unit>",
         "Gain [300]-[2000] [Culture] <by consuming this unit> <before the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Gain [400]-[6000] [Gold] <by consuming this unit> <before the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Gain [600]-[4000] [Culture] <by consuming this unit> <starting from the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Gain [500]-[10000] [Gold] <by consuming this unit> <starting from the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Great Person - [Culture]",
         "Unbuildable",
         "Uncapturable"
    ],
    "movement": 3
  },
  {
    "name": "Great Orator",
    "unitType": "Civilian",
    "uniques": [
         "Comment [-Masters of rhetoric, persuasion, and speaking confidently on subjects they barely understand.\nA skilled orator can calm a riot, inspire a nation, or convince thousands to support a terrible idea.\nTheir greatest weapon is not the sword, but the unsettling realization that people are actually listening.\n• Great Person]",
         "Empire enters a [10]-turn Golden Age <by consuming this unit>",
         "Gain [400]-[3000] [Culture] <by consuming this unit> <before the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Gain [800]-[5000] [Culture] <by consuming this unit> <starting from the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Village] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Great Person - [Propagandhi]",
         "Unbuildable",
         "Uncapturable"
],
    "movement": 3
  },
  {
    "name": "Great Scholar",
    "unitType": "Civilian",
    "uniques": [
         "Comment [-Philosophers, mathematicians, physicians, and other individuals cursed with curiosity.\nThey spend decades searching for truth, only for rulers to ask whether their discoveries can improve taxes or win wars.\nFortunately, knowledge survives longer than kingdoms. Unfortunately, so do some diseases.\n• Great Person]",
         "Empire enters a [12]-turn Golden Age <by consuming this unit>",
         "[1] free random researchable Tech(s) from the [Archaic Age] <by consuming this unit> <during the [Archaic Age]>",
         "Gain [500]-[1500] [Science] <by consuming this unit> <before the [Classical Age]>",
         "Gain [700]-[2500] [Science] <by consuming this unit> <during the [Classical Age]>",
         "Gain [1000]-[3500] [Science] <by consuming this unit> <starting from the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Remove [DANGEROUS PLAGUE] [in all cities] <[2] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Village] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
         "Great Person - [Science]",
         "Unbuildable",
         "Uncapturable"
    ],
    "movement": 3
  },
  {
    "name": "Great Merchant",
    "unitType": "Civilian",
    "uniques": [
         "Comment [-Merchants whose wealth exceeds the treasury of lesser kingdoms.\nThey travel vast distances in pursuit of profit, bringing exotic goods, valuable contacts, and creative interpretations of local tax laws.\nWhere armies see enemies and scholars see mysteries, merchants see potential customers.\n• Great Person]",
         "Empire enters a [12]-turn Golden Age <by consuming this unit>",
         "Can undertake a trade mission with City-State, giving a large sum of gold and [150] Influence",
         "Gain [800]-[8000] [Gold] <by consuming this unit> <before the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Gain [1200]-[12000] [Gold] <by consuming this unit> <starting from the [Hellenistic Age]>",
         "Can instantly construct a [Trading post] improvement <[1] times> <after which this unit is consumed>",
